description: This trap will be sent any time a service incident is logged or
updated. A service incident is generated when it is determined that
a service event has occurred based upon an analysis of system
initiated event traps or an update to a service event has occurred.
User Action: None Required
-- (the argument consists of the
-- following:
-- - text string containing a brief description of the
-- event type with an associated url pointing to a
-- description of the service event provided by
-- OSEM/MSADB
-- - text containing the device name with an associated
-- URL pointing to the server agent that initiated the
-- event.
-- - the Event Time)
objects.test: $SNMPTRAPCMD CPQSERVICE-MIB::cpqServiceInformation RFC1213-MIB::sysName s EXAMPLE CPQSERVICE-MIB::cpqServiceIncidentSeverity i 1 CPQSERVICE-MIB::cpqServiceIncidentStatus i 1 CPQSERVICE-MIB::cpqServiceIncidentInformation s EXAMPLE CPQSERVICE-MIB::cpqServiceIncidentEvent s EXAMPLE CPQSERVICE-MIB::cpqServiceIncidentUniqueID s EXAMPLE CPQSERVICE-MIB::cpqServiceIncidentTimeofOriginalEvent s EXAMPLE CPQSERVICE-MIB::cpqServiceIncidentSourceSystemName s EXAMPLE CPQSERVICE-MIB::cpqServiceIncidentIPAddessOfSource a 192.0.2.1 CPQSERVICE-MIB::cpqServiceISEEIncidentInformation s EXAMPLE CPQSERVICE-MIB::cpqServiceIncidentIdentifier s EXAMPLE CPQSERVICE-MIB::cpqServiceIncidentReceiveTrapOID o 1.3.6.1.4.1.8072.2.1.1 CPQSERVICE-MIB::cpqServiceIncidentFilterOID o 1.3.6.1.4.1.8072.2.1.1 CPQSERVICE-MIB::cpqServiceIncidentFilterValue s EXAMPLE
